name: BIGPIN
description:
Bigpin is an award-winning performing artist, songwriter, content creator, digital marketing specialist and actor from Nairobi. The charismatic lyricist is a trailblazer of Kenya‚Äôs Urban Hip Hop and Kapuka sound. As one of the pioneers of this music revolution, he played a pivotal role in shifting the local entertainment scene from Western-dominated airwaves to homegrown Kenyan beats, sparking a mass cultural movement toward embracing local music. His efforts saw him crowned as the Best Male Artist in East Africa at the prestigious KORA Awards in 2004.

Bigpin‚Äôs music transcended borders, taking him to stages across the globe. His international tours and performances have helped carry Kenyan music to new audiences while strengthening his connection with the diaspora.

name: Wu-Tang Clan
description:
The Wu-Tang Clan is an American hip hop group from Staten Island, New York City, originally composed of East Coast rappers RZA, GZA, Ol' Dirty Bastard, Method Man, Raekwon, Ghostface Killah, Inspectah Deck, U-God and Masta Killa. Cappadonna later became an official member of the group. The Wu-Tang Clan has released four gold and platinum studio albums. Its 1993 debut album, Enter the Wu-Tang (36 Chambers), is considered to be one of the greatest albums in hip-hop history.

The Wu-Tang Clan has introduced and launched the careers of a number of affiliated artists and groups, often collectively known as the Wu-Tang Killa Bees, and has been described as one of the most influential hip-hop groups of all-time. In 2008, About ranked them "the No. 1 greatest hip hop group of all time". Kris Ex of Rolling Stone called Wu-Tang Clan "the best rap group ever".  In 2004, NME hailed them as one of the most influential groups of the last ten years.

name: Mutoriah
description:
Meet Mutoriah, the artist-producer. With his soulful voice and heartfelt lyrics, Mutoriah draws inspiration from a range of genres to create his signature sound - Electro AfroPop.

In 2016, Mutoriah's career took off when he joined Calif Records as a resident producer. From there, he co-founded his own record label, Me & My Cousin Entertainment, and began producing hit records for several artists, including Ayrosh, Serro, and Wanavokali.

In 2019, Mutoriah released his debut album, "Dive In," which received critical acclaim and has been worldwide. Since then, he has continued to release new music, including the album 'Happiness', the hit single "I Want" with Chris Kaiga, and "Presha," which landed a Netflix sync deal for the Kenyan film "Christmas Love."

For Mutoriah, He sees music as a way to connect with others and share his experiences. Whether you're going through a tough time or just looking for some inspiration, his music is sure to resonate with you.

description: Formed in 2008, Swedish House Mafia‚ÄîAxwell, Steve Angello, and Sebastian Ingrosso‚Äîquickly became global icons in electronic music. They brought house to arenas, sold out Madison Square Garden, and closed Coachella‚Äôs main stage. Their hits ‚ÄúSave the World‚Äù and ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt You Worry Child‚Äù earned GRAMMY¬Æ nominations and multi-platinum status. After a record-breaking farewell tour and five-year hiatus, they returned at Ultra 2018 and launched the Save The World Reunion Tour. In 2022, they released Paradise Again, their first full-length album, featuring The Weeknd, Sting, and more. It debuted at #1 on Billboard‚Äôs Dance chart. Singles like ‚ÄúMoth To A Flame‚Äù became global hits. They headlined Coachella again and toured 29 cities worldwide. In 2025, they launched SUPERHUMAN, their creative home and label, debuting solo and collaborative tracks and spotlighting new talent. With new music, major shows, and bold ambition, Swedish House Mafia 3.0 is in full force.

name: Martin Garrix
description: Multi-platinum-selling, chart-topping Dutch DJ and producer Martin Garrix is one of the most successful artists to break into the pop and electronic music scenes. Since his breakout hit "Animals" in 2013 at just 17 years old, Garrix has headlined festivals globally and collaborated with top stars including Dua Lipa, Bono, The Edge, Macklemore, and Khalid. Known for his high-energy performances and infectious productions, Garrix has performed at the Winter Olympics (2018), Coachella, Lollapalooza, Ultra Music Festival, Tomorrowland, and was named the Official UEFA Euro 2020 music artist, where he produced the official song for the tournament as well as other key music at the finals. Today, Garrix continues to connect with audiences worldwide, solidifying his place as a pioneer in electronic music. Climbing yet another rung of his ladder to stardom, he is a founder of his very own label (STMPD RCRDS), owner of a studio complex in Amsterdam, and a mentor to upcoming artists.

name: Everyday Astronaut
description:
Rocket science. A term we all use to describe something incredibly difficult. Trying to grasp all of the concepts involved in rocket science can be incredibly intimidating.

My name‚Äôs Tim Dodd but I'm better known as the Everyday Astronaut. Recently I fell head over heels in love with spaceflight. My appreciation and curiosity for the subject grew into an obsession. Before you knew it, all I wanted to do was learn more and more... the more I learned, the more I wanted to share what was making me so excited. 

But as someone who dropped out of college and has no technical background or degree‚Ä¶ I really felt unqualified for the job of explaining rocket science to anyone. But the fact of the matter is, if I can learn this stuff, anyone can. 

Rocket science is awesome, and you don‚Äôt need to be a rocket scientist to be excited. 

Everyday Astronaut. Bringing space down to Earth for everyday people.

Dorphan is a gifted lyrical virtuoso ‚Äì a blender of verse, hip hop, theatre, music and improv in his mission to be a truth-teller, a historian of self and society. He opens the door to vulnerability and poignancy so rare in performance spaces chasing the momentary relief of comedy and lets the tirades verbalizing the pains of dispossession flow freely ‚Äì telling the stories of the forgotten, the scarred, and the disenfranchised peoples ‚Äì from the juicy bustle of Meru‚Äôs Gakoromone Market to the mad flavours of Eastlands Nairobi.
#Dorphanage

name: Alaine
description:
Alaine Laughton (born September 21, 1978), known by her first name, is a reggae singer and songwriter.[1] She was born in New Jersey, but moved to Jamaica at the age of three.

In 1988, Alaine appeared in movie Clara's Heart alongside Whoopi Goldberg.[2] Through the late 1990s and early 2000s, Alaine lived in the United States and did songwriting and singing back up for Rocafella artists such as Cam'ron and Freeway.

She moved back to Jamaica in the summer of 2004 to focus on her own music after working as an investment banker for JPMorgan Chase. Alaine later met with Craig "Serani" Marsh of DASECA, and started working with him. Their immediate chemistry provided Alaine with her first song on the radio within days of her arrival back to Jamaica.

In 2005 single "No Ordinary Love" on Don Corleon's Seasons Riddim (Sean Paul, T.O.K.) was a breakthrough single in the reggae scene, and Alaine was quickly praised for her special talents.

name: Diaper Mentality
description:
In comparison to other countries, Kenya is considered a "young" nation. Unfortunately, some of our countrymen and women take this compliment literally, and behave like the little ones. Just like children, they do their 'business' in public which is embarrassing to them and those around them. Hence the title, 'Diaper Mentality' as diapers come in handy, and shields them from making embarrassing displays. 

Many Kenyan adults, in spite of their age, display a 'diaper mentality'. They seem unable or unwilling to take charge of their lives, or act responsibly -- be it in their personal/public affairs, or even taking up their civic responsibility -- even when the consequences of their actions are detrimental to their well-being; while it is well within their power to act differently and achieve a more positive outcome. The most common being accepting a bribe for a vote, then spend five years complaining about the ineptitude of the leaders put in place.
